description:
&lt;p&gt;STAFF BANK AND AGENCY SERVICE&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Do you want to be paid at a rate that reflects your skills and experience?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Do you want to work flexible hours?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Would you like to be valued as individual employee?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If so then come and join County Durham and Darlington NHS Foundation Trust as one of our valued bank workers. Following a review of the current pay points for our bank workers these now reflect the value that our bank staff provide our organisation. The Staff Bank and Agency Service was re-launched in August last year and is working to provide a complete temporary staffing solution for all of our wards and departments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting time to join us as the service is transforming and developing into an innovative and modern provider of temporary staffing. You will need to be a registered nurse (Adult) with a valid NMC number. You will need to be a reliable, enthusiastic and a self-motivated individual, You will need to possess excellent communication skills and be adaptable to changing situations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is essential that you are reliable, punctual and work well within a team environment, as well as working under Trust Policy and the NMC Code of Conduct. Our Bank operates like an internal agency, booking temporary staff on a flexible basis. It gives you the freedom to choose the shifts you work, depending upon availability.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Benefits include: • Pension Scheme • Flexible working hours • Opportunity to work in different areas/settings • Paid attendance at mandatory training courses If you are flexible and adaptable, have a keen interest in working with people and are looking for a challenge, please apply now!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are not recruiting Bank Registered Nurses (Learning Disabilities) or Bank Registered Nurses (Mental Health) at this time.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;IF YOU ARE ALREADY AN EMPLOYEE OF CDDFT AND WOULD LIKE TO DO BANK WORK, YOU DO NOT NEED TO APPLY. INSTEAD PLEASE EMAIL: cdda-tr.bank@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
